    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "text": "Rust is a [multi-paradigm](/wiki/Multi-paradigm_programming_language) , general-purpose [programming language](/wiki/Programming_language) that emphasizes performance, type safety, and [concurrency](/wiki/Concurrency_(computer_science)) . It enforces memory safety—meaning that all references point to valid memory—without a traditional [garbage collector](/wiki/Garbage_collection_(computer_science)) .",
